  <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

  <p>Before founding Inkcap Consulting, Rogers spent more than fifteen years in administrative, research, and teaching roles:</p>

  <ul class="experience-list">
    <li>Co-director of the <a href="http://futuresinitiative.org">Futures Initiative</a> at CUNY (2014–2021)</li>
    <li>Co-director of <a href="http://cunyhumanitiesalliance.org">CUNY Humanities Alliance</a> (2014–2021)</li>
    <li>Director of Programs and Administration at <a href="http://hastac.org">HASTAC</a> (2014–2021)</li>
    <li>Adjunct faculty in GC's Master's Program in Digital Humanities</li>
    <li>Managing editor of <a href="http://commons.mla.org">MLA Commons</a> at the Modern Language Association (2013–2014)</li>
    <li>Postdoctoral researcher with the <a href="http://uvasci.org">Scholarly Communication Institute</a> (2012–2013)</li>
    <li>Strategic contributor to the <a href="http://www.sloan.org/">Alfred P. Sloan Foundation</a>'s Digital Information Technology program (2009–2012)</li>
    <li>Language and literature instructor at <a href="http://colorado.edu/">University of Colorado, Boulder</a> (2004–2009)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Approach</h2>

  <div class="section-accent">
    <p>As a humanities PhD and a higher education expert with over a decade of experience, Katina Rogers has a deep understanding of the importance of continually working to improve and update program structures—as well as the challenges and political sensitivities inherent in the task. Inkcap creates frameworks that are supportive, sustainable, research-driven, and community-oriented.</p>

    <p>Equity, sustainability, engagement, and community are focal points in all aspects of Inkcap's work. We help institutions to develop policies and practices that support retention and wellbeing of faculty, students, and staff, while also fostering creative and high-impact scholarship that goes beyond the walls of the university.</p>
